<br>
<br>
The only thing EQ puts in the Windows Registry are Uninstall pointers.  It is a self standing program (this was posted to the Dev Corner a while back).<br>
<br>
<br>
Since Uninstalling EQ is something done very rarely, it's not really an issue.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, I have tested this on 2 systems.  Both transfering EQ to my new box (which STILL isn't stable), and moving it from my C drive to my D drive on my main system.  No problems from EQ. <p><TABLE ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=460 COLS=1 BORDER=1 BGCOLOR=#FF0000>
