</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uadaaeldarksmith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adaael Darksmith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 1:48:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Transferring between computers</span><hr size=1> As others have said, the simplest thing to do is just copy your entire Everquest directory to the new computer, and then go find Everquest.exe and make a shortcut on your desktop or in your start menu.  That's it, in most cases.<br>
<br>
However, if one computer has a Voodoo and one does not, this can confuse EQ about the video card settings, and you'll get a crash when you try to go to the server selection screen.  To fix that crash, you have to go to options and change your video selection (EVEN IF THE VIDEO SELECTION IS CORRECT!) and try again (and then go change it back if it was originally correct and try again).<br>
<br>
